stand and share the root cause of changes the team makes to those KPIs. Communicate test results and findings to product and tech teams. <br /><br /><br /><br /></li></ul><strong>Requirements<br /></strong><ul><li>3+ years experience with analysis preferably for an ecommerce company</li><li>BA/BS in Statistics, Economics, Math, Computer Science, or other quantitative field. MS/PhD preferred but not required</li><li>Understanding of statistical analysis, experience with packages such as R, pandas. </li><li>Solid understanding of statistical modeling/machine learning/ data mining/ recommender systems concepts.</li><li>Amazing written and verbal communication skills</li><li>SQL Fluent with some development experience in at least one scripting language ( Python, R, sh, etc.)</li><li>Experience working with large data sets within MPP databases and MapReduce paradigm a plus</li><li>Ability to initiate and drive projects to completion with minimal guidance</li><li>Comfortable with *nix</li><li>The ability to communicate the results of analyses in a clear and effective manner</li><li>Experience working with mobile and website event data to perform behavioral analytics and AB/multivariate testing<br /><br /></li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Founded in 2007, Gilt, www.gilt.com, is an innovative online shopping destination offering its members special access to the most inspiring merchandise and experiences every day at insider prices. Gilt pioneered “flash sales” in the United States and today is one of the leaders in the flash-sale space. <br /><br />Gilt continually searches the world for the most coveted brands and products, including fashion for women, men, and children; home decor; and unique activities in select cities and destinations. Our business is driving economic growth across the globe for fashion, design, home goods and experiences.</div>